OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FTwo brothers have been found guilty of
OL,7,Fkilling a civil servant 42 years ago
OL,8,Fduring a spree of gratuitous violence
OL,9,Fagainst gay men.
OL,11,FMichael Stewart, 57, and Anthony
OL,12,FStewart, 60, were just 15 and 18 when
OL,13,Fthey set upon Anthony Littler as he
OL,14,Fwalked home in East Finchley, north
OL,15,FLondon, on May 1, 1984.
OL,17,FMr Littler, 45, was hit twice over the
OL,18,Fhead with a blunt weapon and was found
OL,19,Fmortally wounded half an hour later,
OL,20,Fstill with his briefcase, #80 cash and
OL,21,Fcredit cards.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FWithin minutes of the attack, Michael
OL,7,FStewart had anonymously called for an
OL,8,Fambulance from a phone box, but a
OL,9,Fsearch for an injured man was called
OL,10,Foff after he hung up.
OL,12,FHalf an hour later, Mr Littler was
OL,13,Ffound by members of the public lying
OL,14,Fin a pool of blood in an alleyway
OL,15,Fhaving suffered a "catastrophic" brain
OL,16,Finjury.
OL,18,FBy the spring of 1984 the Stewart
OL,19,Fsiblings and their friends had made a
OL,20,F"hobby" of targeting lone men who they
OL,21,Fbelieved to be gay, jurors were told.
OL,26,@wD@SOUwD@`O]|D@AOU|D@GO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FBut during house-to-house police
OL,7,Finquiries, they claimed to be at home
OL,8,Fat the time of the attack on Mr
OL,9,FLittler, with binman Anthony Stewart
OL,10,Finsisting he never used the alley.
OL,12,FDespite an appeal on BBC Crimewatch
OL,13,Fand ITV's Police 5, no meaningful
OL,14,Fleads were identified and the case
OL,15,Fremained unsolved for decades, the Old
OL,16,FBailey heard.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FThe breakthrough came on the 29th
OL,7,Fanniversary of Mr Littler's death,
OL,8,Fwhen the defendants' younger brother
OL,9,FDaniel, who was 10 at the time, came
OL,10,Fforward to police after a family
OL,11,Ffalling-out.
OL,13,FHe told officers his older brothers
OL,14,Fhad confessed to the killing and
OL,15,Fboasted about being involved in "queer
OL,16,Fbashing", jurors were told.
OL,18,FYears after the killing, Michael
OL,19,FStewart had also admitted his guilt to
OL,20,Fa girlfriend and even showed her where
OL,21,Fit happened, the court had heard.
OL,26,@wD@aOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FIn 2022, police reopened the
OL,7,Finvestigation and deployed covert
OL,8,Finvestigative techniques against the
OL,9,Fbrothers, bugging their cars and
OL,10,FMichael's home.
OL,12,FAnthony was said to be a man of few
OL,13,Fwords but Michael proved to have a
OL,14,F"loose tongue" and bragged about what
OL,15,Fhe did in 1984, the court heard.
OL,17,FAfter an Old Bailey trial, a jury
OL,18,Fdeliberated for less than three hours
OL,19,Fto find them guilty of murder on
OL,20,FMonday.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@NO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FSenior Crown prosecutor Samantha
OL,7,FYelland said investigators had faced
OL,8,F"challenges" bringing a case, with the
OL,9,Floss of key evidence, including a
OL,10,Fpotential murder weapon.
OL,12,FThe "unusual" decision to deploy
OL,13,Fcovert tactics was made in the absence
OL,14,Fof other evidence to prosecute the
OL,15,Fhistoric hate crime, she said.
OL,17,FAfter the guilty verdicts, Ms Yelland
OL,18,Ftold the Press Association: "I'm so
OL,19,Fpleased that we've managed to get
OL,20,Fjustice all these years later for
OL,21,FAnthony Littler.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@LO]tD@EOUtD@MO]zD@]OU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,F"It's never right that someone dies in
OL,7,Fthese circumstances, in particular in
OL,8,Fa hate crime. I'm glad that we've been
OL,9,Fable to get justice for his family."
OL,11,FDetective Chief Inspector Neil John,
OL,12,Fof Scotland Yard, said: "Anthony's
OL,13,Flife was suddenly cut short when he
OL,14,Fwas killed in a brutal attack by two
OL,15,Fteenagers who we now know had a clear
OL,16,Fpropensity for the most sickening kind
OL,17,Fof violence."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@dO]tD@YOUyD@MOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FThey targeted Anthony because he was
OL,7,Falone, defenceless and walking down a
OL,8,Fdark alley in which they knew no-one
OL,9,Fwould see them carrying out their
OL,10,Fhorrendous assault.
OL,12,F"They lay in wait for someone to cross
OL,13,Ftheir path, and tragically for Anthony
OL,14,Fhe became their unsuspecting victim."
OL,16,FWe know Anthony's murder has continued
OL,17,Fto cause his family pain all these
OL,18,Fyears later, and we are pleased that
OL,19,Fthey now know who was responsible for
OL,20,Fhis death."
OL,26,@tD@AOUvD@eOU|D@KO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FDuring their trial, prosecutor John
OL,7,FPrice KC had described the events
OL,8,Fleading up to Mr Littler's death.
OL,10,FThe real ale enthusiast had spent the
OL,11,Fevening at a pub in Carshalton,
OL,12,FSurrey, at a meeting of the Ponds
OL,13,FBranch of The Society for the
OL,14,FPreservation of Beer from the Wood.
OL,16,FHe arrived at East Finchley Tube
OL,17,Fstation at 12.18am on May 1 and walked
OL,18,Fdown a narrow alleyway, where he was
OL,19,Fattacked.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FMr Price said the assailants lay in
OL,7,Fwait and "ambushed" Mr Littler,
OL,8,Fimmediately striking him over the
OL,9,Fhead, even though there was no
OL,10,Fevidence they knew their victim.
OL,12,FHe suggested they may have panicked
OL,13,Fand fled the scene without going
OL,14,Fthrough his pockets when it became
OL,15,Fclear from the amount of blood that
OL,16,Fthey had killed him.
OL,18,FLate resident Edward Dyer had been
OL,19,Fwalking his dog and heard a loud shout
OL,20,Fwhich "sounded like a cry of pain",
OL,21,Fjurors were told.
OL,26,@oD@JOUoD@SO]|D@GOU|D@bO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FAbout half an hour later, Annalieze
OL,7,Fand James Hainge found Mr Littler
OL,8,Flying injured in the alleyway as they
OL,9,Fwalked home from the station.
OL,11,FMrs Hainge ran to call emergency
OL,12,Fservices from a phone box while her
OL,13,Fhusband stayed with Mr Littler.
OL,15,FHe had two skull fractures and a
OL,16,F"catastrophic brain injury" from which
OL,17,Fhe died at the scene.
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FMrs Hainge's call to emergency
OL,7,Fservices had been the second 999 alert
OL,8,Ffrom a public phone kiosk, jurors were
OL,9,Ftold.
OL,11,FAt 12.22am, an unknown person had
OL,12,Fcalled an operator and asked for an
OL,13,F"ambulance ` quick".
OL,15,FHe told her: "I can't stop, just get
OL,16,Fan ambulance to East Finchley station,
OL,17,Fthere's a man hurt outside the
OL,18,Fstation."
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@SO]wD@NOUzD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40913
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FLondon Ambulance Service recorded the
OL,7,Fcaller saying the casualty was
OL,8,F"bleeding heavily" before putting the
OL,9,Fphone down.
OL,11,FThe call handler had noted the male
OL,12,Fseemed "abnormally concerned over the
OL,13,Fmatter", was "well spoken" and had a
OL,14,F"young sounding voice".
OL,16,FStation staff searched the area and
OL,17,Ffound no trace of a bleeding man so
OL,18,Fthe incident was stood down, the court
OL,19,Fwas told.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@RO]tD@HOUuD@GO]uD@NOUuD@ZO]vD@
OL,26,AAOUvD@VO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40914
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FMr Price told jurors that given the
OL,7,Ftiming of the call, the unknown person
OL,8,Fmust have been there when Mr Littler
OL,9,Fwas attacked but gave "wholly
OL,10,Finaccurate information".
OL,12,FHe said: "The prosecution submits that
OL,13,F42 years later, the evidence now
OL,14,Favailable shows that it was Michael
OL,15,FStewart who had made that first 999
OL,16,Fcall at 12.22am and then hung up
OL,17,Fwithout giving the operator his name
OL,18,For the information she needed."
OL,26,@qD@WOUrD@WO]tD@JOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G14/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40915
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1780575067
OL,3,CBrothers guilty of 1984 hate crime
OL,4,Ckilling of civil servant
OL,6,FBoth defendants, from north London,
OL,7,Fwho declined to give evidence, had
OL,8,Fdenied involvement.After the guilty
OL,9,Fverdicts, the brothers were remanded
OL,10,Finto custody to be sentenced on July 3.
OL,12,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,13,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,14,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,15,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,16,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,17,Fbelow...
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G15/15
